Here's a simple XAML page for a stopwatch using WPF. This example includes a `Button` to start/stop the timer, two `TextBlock`s to display the elapsed time and elapsed minutes/seconds, and a `DockPanel` to keep everything aligned.

```xaml
<Window x:Class="StopwatchApp.MainWindow"
