```

### CSS
CSS for Styling the Iframe
```css
/* styles.css */
.iframe-container {
  width: 100%;
  overflow: hidden;
}

#responsive-iframe {
  display: block;
  width: 100%;
  height: 500px; /* Set a fixed height or adjust as needed */
  border: none; /* Remove default border */
}

/* Responsive adjustments */
@media (min-width: 361px) {
  #responsive-iframe {
    width: 100%;
  }
}

@media (min-width: 721px) {
  #responsive-iframe {
    width: 100%;
  }
}

@media (min-width: 1401px) {
  #responsive-iframe {
    width: 100%;
  }
}
```

### JavaScript
JavaScript for Handling Responsive Width Changes
```javascript
// script.js

window.addEventListener('resize', function() {
  const ifr = document.getElementById('responsive-iframe');
  if (window.innerWidth >= 361 && window.innerWidth < 720) {
    ifr.width = '360px';
  } else if (window.innerWidth >= 721 && window.innerWidth < 1400) {
    ifr.width = '720px';
  } else if (window.innerWidth >= 1400) {
    ifr.width = '1400px';
  } else {
    ifr.width = '100%';
  }
});

// Initial check
window.addEventListener('load', function() {
  adjustIframeWidth();
});

function adjustIframeWidth() {
  if (window.innerWidth >= 361 && window.innerWidth < 720) {
    document.getElementById('responsive-iframe').width = '360px';
  } else if (window.innerWidth >= 721 && window.innerWidth < 1400) {
    document.getElementById('responsive-iframe').width = '720px';
  } else if (window.innerWidth >= 1400) {
    document.getElementById('responsive-iframe').width = '1400px';
  } else {
    document.getElementById('responsive-iframe').width = '100%';
  }
}
```

### Explanation
1. **HTML**: Contains a container for the `iframe` and the links to the CSS and JavaScript files.
2. **CSS**: Styles the `iframe` to take the full width of the container and adds media queries to adjust the width of the `iframe` based on the screen width.
3. **JavaScript**: Adds an event listener to adjust the `iframe`'s width when the window is resized. Additionally, it sets the width on initial load.

This code effectively makes the `iframe` responsive based on different screen widths.

