Alright, let's walk through how we can achieve this. Here’s a step-by-step guide to implementing a navigation bar that hides and shows with sliding animation on scroll down and scroll up, while also disabling the animation for pages that don't need to scroll plus some slack.

### Step 1: HTML Structure
Ensure you have the navigation bar and the content in your HTML:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Scroll Navigation</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <nav id="navbar" class="navbar">
        <a href="#">Home</a>
        <a href="#">About</a>
        <a href="#">Services</a>
        <a href="#">Contact</a>
    </nav>
    <div class="content">
        <p>Your content goes here...</p>
        <!-- Add more content to make the page scrollable -->
    </div>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

### Step 2: CSS for Styling
Create `styles.css` to style the navigation bar and its sliding animation:

```css
.navbar {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    background-color: #333;
    color: white;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-around;
    padding: 1rem;
    transform: translateY(0);
    transition: transform 0.3s ease-in-out;
    z-index: 1000;
}

.navbar a {
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: 0.5rem;
}

.content {
    padding-top: 4rem; /* Adjust this value to match the height of the navbar */
    height: 200vh; /* Example height to ensure the page is scrollable */
}

.hidden {
    transform: translateY(-100%);
}
```

### Step 3: JavaScript for Scroll Handling
Create `script.js` to handle the scroll events and apply the sliding.animation:

```javascript
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const navbar = document.getElementById('navbar');
    let lastScrollTop = 0;
    let slack = 50; // Slack value for non-scrolling pages

    function scrollHandler() {
        const currentScrollPosition = window.pageYOffset || document.documentElement.scrollTop;

        if (currentScrollPosition > lastScrollTop) {
            // Scrolling down
            navbar.classList.add('hidden');
        } else {
            // Scrolling up
            navbar.classList.remove('hidden');
        }

        lastScrollTop = currentScrollPosition;
    }

    // Attach the scroll event listener
    window.addEventListener('scroll', scrollHandler);

    // Additional logic for pages that don't need to scroll plus some slack
    setInterval(() => {
        if (document.documentElement.scrollHeight - window.innerHeight < 200) { // Example check for small page
            navbar.classList.add('disable-animation');
        } else {
            navbar.classList.remove('disable-animation');
        }
